SIMPLE: prejudicial
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prejudicial
<hw>Prej`u*di"cial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praejudicialis</ets> belonging to a preceding judgment: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧judiciel</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Biased, possessed, or blinded by prejudices; <as>as,
to look with a <ex>prejudicial</ex> eye</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holyday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tending to obstruct or impair; hurtful; injurious;
disadvantageous; detrimental.</def> <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His going away . . . was most <qex>prejudicial</qex> and most
ruinous to the king's affairs.</q> <rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Prej`u*di"cial*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Prej`u*di"cial*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preknowledge</ent>⟦br⟧
